
<!doctype html>
%html{:lang => "en"}
  %head
    %meta{:charset => "utf-8"}/
    %meta{:content => "width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0", :name => "viewport"}/
    %title Blog Layout Example – Pure
    %link{:href => "http://yui.yahooapis.com/pure/0.2.0/pure-min.css", :rel => "stylesheet"}/
    %link{:href => "/combo/1.3.7?/css/layouts/blog.css", :rel => "stylesheet"}/
    %link(rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheet/style.css")
  %body
    #layout.pure-g-r
      .sidebar.pure-u
        %header.header.pure-u-1
          %hgroup
            %h1.brand-title rtc
            %h2.brand-tagline skype in the browser
          %nav.nav
            %ul.nav-list
              %li.nav-item
                %a.pure-button{:href => "http://spitfiresky.com/blog/getting-started-with-sinatra.html"} Sinatra
              %li.nav-item
                %a.pure-button{:href => "https://vline.com/developer/docs/getting_started"} V-Line
      .content.pure-u-1
        / A wrapper for all the blog posts
        .posts.pure-g
          %h1.content-subhead.pure-u-1 Pinned Post
          / A single blog post
          %section.post.pure-u-1
            %header.post-header
              / %img.post-avatar{:alt => "Tilo Mitra's avatar", :height => "48", :src => "/img/common/tilo-avatar.png", :width => "128"}/
              %h2.post-title.pure-u-1 Testing rtc
              / %p.post-meta.pure-u-1
              /   By
              /   %a.post-author{:href => "#"} Tilo Mitra
              /   under
              /   %a.post-category.post-category-design{:href => "#"} CSS
              /   %a.post-category.post-category-pure{:href => "#"} Pure
            .post-description.pure-u-1
              %p
                Yesterday at CSSConf, we launched Pure – a new CSS library. Phew! Here are the
                = succeed "." do
                  %a{:href => "https://speakerdeck.com/tilomitra/pure-bliss"} slides from the presentation
                Although it looks pretty minimalist, we’ve been working on Pure for several months. After many iterations, we have released Pure as a set of small, responsive, CSS modules that you can use in every web project.
       
        %footer.footer
          .pure-menu.pure-menu-horizontal.pure-menu-open
            %ul
              %li
                %a{:href => "http://purecss.io/"} About
              %li
                %a{:href => "http://twitter.com/yuilibrary/"} Twitter
              %li
                %a{:href => "http://github.com/yui/pure/"} Github